<subSubSection id="C5BCF8D2320DFFF55CBA00D6FE84FE98" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8D19AB59320DFFF55CBA00D6FD0CFF08" blockId="3.[174,760,175,202]" box="[174,760,175,202]" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">
<heading id="D6511C35320DFFF55CBA00D6FD0CFF08" box="[174,760,175,202]" fontSize="36" level="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" reason="3">
<taxonomicName id="4AA6D0DA320DFFF55CBA00D6FD0CFF08" authority="Rondani, 1857" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1857" box="[174,760,175,202]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laticornis" subGenus="Convocheila">
<emphasis id="BFD2774B320DFFF55CBA00D6FDB3FF08" bold="true" box="[174,583,175,202]" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis id="BFD2774B320DFFF55CBA00D6FEEAFF08" bold="true" box="[174,286,175,202]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Cheilosia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="BFD2774B320DFFF55D3B00D6FE30FF08" bold="true" box="[303,452,175,202]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Convocheila</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="BFD2774B320DFFF55DC100D6FDB3FF08" bold="true" box="[469,583,175,202]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">laticornis</emphasis>
</emphasis>
Rondani, 1857
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D19AB59320DFFF55CF70099FE84FE98" blockId="3.[174,1233,223,442]" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. From From Fennoscandia southwards to Iberian Peninsula and from 
<collectingCountry id="F5B1EBC9320DFFF55CBA0086FEF7FEDB" box="[174,259,255,281]" name="Ireland" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Ireland</collectingCountry>
eastwards through Central and Southern Europe to 
<collectingCountry id="F5B1EBC9320DFFF55F7B0086FC30FEDB" box="[879,964,255,281]" name="Turkey" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Turkey</collectingCountry>
and on into European territory of 
<collectingCountry id="F5B1EBC9320DFFF55D280166FE7CFEFB" box="[316,392,287,313]" name="Russia" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Russia</collectingCountry>
and western Siberia. Also in Northern Africa (
<bibRefCitation id="E937D6A8320DFFF55FD70166FB73FEF8" author="Kassebeer, C. F." box="[963,1159,287,314]" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" pagination="57 - 68" refId="ref6624" refString="Kassebeer, C. F. Die marokkanischen Arten der Gattung Cheilosia Meigen, 1822 (Diptera, Syrphidae) // Dipteron. - 1998. - 1. - P. 57 - 68." type="book chapter" year="1998">Kassebeer, 1998</bibRefCitation>
); 
<collectingCountry id="F5B1EBC9320DFFF5588A0159FB24FEF8" box="[1182,1232,288,314]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E937D6A8320DFFF55CA20146FE97FE98" author="Gilasian, E." box="[182,355,319,346]" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" pagination="75 - 76" refId="ref6509" refString="Gilasian, E. New record of one genus and six species of Syrphidae (Diptera) from Iran // J. Entomological Society of Iran. - 2005. - 25, N 1. - P. 75 - 76." type="book chapter" year="2005">Gilasian, 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C5BCF8D2320DFFF55CF70119FBADFE7B" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" type="description">
<paragraph id="8D19AB59320DFFF55CF70119FBADFE7B" blockId="3.[174,1233,223,442]" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">D i a g n o s t i c c h a r a c t e r s. Eye bare; eye margin below antenna with long hairs, third antennal segment reddish-black; dorsal side of facial knob bare, at most with very short hairs, tibia pale at the both ends, hind margin of scutellum without bristle.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
